Compute, export and save statistics

Source: R/cyto_stats_compute.R
cyto_stats_compute.Rd

Compute, export and save statistics

cyto_stats_compute(
  x,
  alias = NULL,
  parent = NULL,
  channels = NULL,
  trans = NA,
  stat = NULL,
  inverse = TRUE,
  round = 2,
  format = "wide",
  tibble = FALSE,
  input = "matrix",
  smooth = 1,
  bins = 256,
  details = TRUE,
  markers = TRUE,
  save_as = NULL,
  select = NULL,
  ...
)

Arguments

x

object of class cytoset, GatingHierarchy or GatingSet.
alias

names of the populations in the GatingHerarchy or GatingSet for which statistics should be computed.
parent

names of the parent populations in the GatingHierarchy or GatingSet required when computing frequency statistics. When stat = "freq" the frequency of each alias population will be computed as a proportion of each parent population.
channels

names of the channels or markers for which statistics should be computed, set to all channels with marker assignments by default.
trans

an object of class transformerList containing the transformers used to transform the channels of the supplied data. The transformerList will be automatically extracted from the GatingHierarchy or GatingSet, so this argument is only required for cytoframes or cytosets. The transformerList is passed to cyto_apply which will make sure the data is appropriately transformed based on inverse prior to passing the data to the desired statistical function.
stat

name of a statistic to compute, options include:

  • count - number of events

  • freq/percent - frequency of population(s) in parent population(s)

  • mean - arithmetic mean

  • geomean - geometric (graphical) mean computed as the inverse of the arithmetic mean on the transformed scale

  • median - 50th quantile

  • mode - inverse of mode on transformed scale computed using smooth and bandwidth to control the smoothness of the density distribution

  • sd - standard deviation

  • rsd - robust standard deviation (less influence of outliers)

  • cv - coefficient of variation

  • rcv - robust coefficient of variation (less influence of outliers)

  • quantile - quantiles with probabilities supplied to probs

  • range - minima and maxima

  • auc - area under curve using a combination of density(), splinefun() and integrate()

stat dispatches through cyto_apply so any custom function can be named through this argument as well. See cyto_apply for details.
inverse

logical passed to cyto_apply to indicate whether transformations applied to the data should be reversed prior to passing the data to the desired statistical function, set to TRUE by default.
round

numeric indicating the number of decimal places to round the computed statistic, set to 2 decimal places by default.
format

can be either "wide" or "long" to control the format of the returned statistics, set to "wide" by default.
tibble

logical indicating whether the statistics should be returned as tibble instead of a data.frame, set to FALSE by default.
input

passed to cyto_apply to control how the data is formatted prior to passing it to the statistical function, options include:

  • 1 - "cytoframe"

  • 2 - "matrix"

  • 3 - "column" or "channel"

  • 4 - "row" or "cell"

Set to "matrix" by default.
smooth

numeric smoothing parameter passed to stats:density when computing mode and area under the curve statistics, set to 1 by default.
bins

number of bins to use for histograms, set to 256 by default.
details

logical indicating whether to include the cyto_details in the output, set to TRUE by default.
markers

logical indicating whether channels should be converted to markers where possible in the output, set to TRUE by default.
save_as

name of a csv file to which the output should be saved, set to NULL by default to bypass this saving step.
select

named list containing experimental variables to be used to select samples using cyto_select when a cytoset or GatingSet is supplied. Refer to cyto_select for more details.
...

additional arguments passed to the desired statistical function.
gate

a rectangleGate, polygonGate or ellipsoidGate object to apply to each cytoframe prior to computing the desired statistic. This argument has been included for backwards compatibility only and is only valid for cytoframe or cytoset objects.

Value

data.frame or tibble containing the computed statistics in the desired format and optionally a csv file containing the computed statistics.

Author

Dillon Hammill, Dillon.Hammill@anu.edu.au

Examples

library(CytoExploreRData)

# Load in samples
fs <- Activation
gs <- GatingSet(fs)

# Compensation
gs <- cyto_compensate(gs)

# Transformations
gs <- cyto_transform(gs)

#> Insufficient plotting space, transformations have been applied.

# Gating
gs <- cyto_gatingTemplate_apply(gs, Activation_gatingTemplate)

# Compute statistics - median

  alias = "T Cells",
  channels = c("Alexa Fluor 488-A", "PE-A"),
  stat = "median"
)

# Name csv to save results
tempfile <- paste0(tempdir(),
.Platform$file.sep,
"Population-Frequencies.csv")

# Compute frequencies and save to tempfile
cyto_stats_compute(gs,
  alias = c("CD4 T Cells", "CD8 T Cells"),
  parent = c("Live Cells", "T Cells"),
  stat = "freq",
  save_as = tempfile
)
